# Contracts & Law Local Runtime Context

You are working in a local contracts, player-device, or law-enforcement runtime/test hotspot.

Start from touched code/tests in these roots first. Do NOT auto-load `docs/design/core-architecture.md` for local contract-state, police-heat, player-device, or target-selection cleanup.

Read `docs/design/README.md` only to decide whether a domain doc is needed. Load docs only as needed:

1. `docs/design/assassination-contracts.md` for contract semantics
2. `docs/design/law-enforcement.md` for policing/offense semantics
3. `docs/design/world-and-vehicles.md` only when the touched seam changes escape geography or travel-facing behavior
4. `docs/design/weapons-and-ballistics.md` and `docs/design/reloading-system.md` only for optics, hit evaluation, or ammo-quality semantics
5. `docs/design/core-architecture.md` only if the change crosses events, save, persistence, or another domain, or if local intent is unclear
6. `.agent/skills/refactoring-and-test-hygiene/SKILL.md` for local runtime refactor/test cleanup

If the task becomes contract/law data-content, world-target wiring, or cross-domain integration work, switch to `.cursor/rules/assassination-contracts-context.mdc` or `.cursor/rules/law-enforcement-context.mdc`.
